    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/136</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received June 20, 11.15 a.
                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>611. Just had audience with <persName corresp="#p_SSD1">Sazonov</persName> which
                    requested June 6 concerning Poland relief. Delay caused by his absence. Declines
                    passing on proposed plan before conferring with Allies. Furthermore, positively
                    objects to 150,000 soldiers or anything near that number being maintained in
                    Poland. Sent <persName corresp="#p_DFM1">Dearing</persName> to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSD1">Sazonov</persName>’s assistant during Minister’s absence
                    June 10, but was told <persName corresp="#p_SSD1">Sazonov</persName> would pass
                    on question himself. Please advise Embassy further developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
